3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20matter%20if%20the%20group%20is%20private%2C%26quot%3B%20Saper%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20just%20need%20to%20show%20a%20verbally%20false%20statement%20has%20been%20made%20about%20you%20and%20has%20been%20published%20by%20a%20third%20party.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20excludes%20opinions.%20Calling%20someone%20%26quot%3Bvery%20clingy%26quot%3B%20wouldn't%20be%20considered%20defamation%20but%20accusing%20someone%20of%20assault%20or%20drugging%20you%20would%20be%20examples%20of%20statements%20that%20could%20get%20someone%20in%20trouble%20if%20they%20can%20be%20proven%20to%20be%20false%2C%20Saper%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20four%20types%20of%20%26quot%3Bper%20se%20defamation%26quot%3B%20or%20written%20defamation%3A%20accusing%20someone%20of%20a%20crime%20such%20as%20sexual%20assault%3B%20accusing%20someone%20of%20having%20an%20infectious%20disease%3B%20accusing%20someone%20of%20conduct%20that%20would%20impact%20their%20job%3B%20and%20accusing%20someone%20of%20unchastity%20e.g.%20calling%20someone%20a%20%26quot%3Bwhore%2C%26quot%3B%20Saper%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllegations%20of%20defamatory%20statements%20also%20need%20to%20outline%20what%20damages%20were%20incurred%20with%20each%20claim%20which%20Saper%20said%20was%20missing%20from%20the%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESaper's%20advice%3A%20%26quot%3BLimit%20the%20statements%20to%20verifiably%20true%20things.%20Anything%20that%20you%20can%20prove.%20Or%20anything%20that%20squarely%20can%20be%20construed%20as%20an%20opinion.%20'He's%20a%20jerk'%20is%20much%20different%20from%20saying%20'He%20roofied%20me.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20if%20you%20recently%20went%20on%20a%20bad%20date%20and%20feel%20compelled%20to%20shout%20about%20it%20into%20the%20digital%20atmosphere%2C%20you%20can%20%E2%80%94%20just%20be%20mindful%20of%20what%20you%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgossiping-