20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-weapons-ammunition-america-provided-russia-invasion-list-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emissiles%20and%20other%20weapons%20the%20United%20States%20has%20sent%20to%20Ukraine%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20aid%20of%20the%20Eastern%20European%20country's%20defense%20against%20Russian%20forces%2C%20according%20to%20a%20new%20report%20by%20the%20Defense%20Department%20Inspector%20General.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20it's%20not%20the%20first%20time%20the%20Department%20of%20Defense%2C%20one%20of%20the%20most%20well-funded%20federal%20agencies%2C%20has%20lost%20tabs%20on%20weaponry%20and%20equipment%20sent%20to%20other%20countries%20like%20Iraq%2C%20Kuwait%2C%20and%20Yemen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20newly%20released%20and%20partially%20redacted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dodig.mil%2Freports.html%2FArticle%2F3642299%2Fevaluation-of-the-dods-enhanced-end-use-monitoring-of-defense-articles-provided%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%20from%20the%20Defense%20Department%20Inspector%20General%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20more%20than%20%241%20billion%20of%20a%20%241.69%20billion%20worth%20of%20weapons%2C%20including%20attack%20drones%2C%20night-vision%20devices%2C%20and%20Javelin%20anti-tank%20missiles%2C%20that%20were%20sent%20to%20Ukraine%20remain%20%26quot%3Bdelinquent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Department%20of%20Defense%20%26quot%3Bdid%20not%20maintain%20an%20accurate%20inventory%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20weapons%20designated%20for%20%26quot%3Benhanced%20end-use%20monitoring%26quot%3B%20(EEUM)%20that%20were%20delivered%20to%20Ukraine%20and%20%26quot%3Bdid%20not%20fully%20comply%26quot%3B%20with%20requirements%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Inspector%20General's%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ereport.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20unclear%20exactly%20how%20many%20weapons%20were%20considered%20delinquent%2C%20but%20the%20report%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bhigh%20rates%20of%20delinquency%20may%20cor