ies%2C%20Buontempo%20said.%20These%20emissions%20trap%20heat%2C%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecord-ocean-temperatures-california-heat-atmospheric-river-storms-santa-cruz-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eis%20absorbed%20by%20oceans%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20contributor%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fextreme-heat-cost-the-global-economy-an-estimated-16-trillion-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecord%20heat%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20El%20Ni%C3%B1o%2C%20a%20natural%20climate%20pattern%20that%20warms%20the%20Pacific%20Ocean.%20It%20began%20in%20early%20July%2C%20making%20July%20and%20August%20the%20hottest%20months%20of%20the%20year.%20El%20Ni%C3%B1o%20is%20expected%20to%20peak%20this%20month%20or%20next.%20This%20is%20partly%20why%20scientists%20expect%202024%20to%20be%20even%20hotter%20than%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Copernicus%20climate%20scientists%20said%20that%20these%20weren't%20the%20only%20factors%20and%20that%20some%20required%20more%20research.%20They%20pointed%20to%20unusual%20marine%20heat%20waves%20beyond%20the%20Pacific%3B%20Antarctic%20sea%20ice%20that%20temporarily%20reached%20record%20lows%3B%20and%20an%20underwater%20volcano%20that%20erupted%20in%202022%20near%20Tonga%2C%20an%20island%20in%20the%20Pacific%2C%20and%20spewed%20water%20vapor%20%E2%80%94%20a%20powerful%20greenhouse%20gas%20%E2%80%94%20into%20the%20atmosphere.%20They%20also%20said%20it%20was%20unclear%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fatmosphere.copernicus.eu%2Faerosols-are-so2-emissions-reductions-contributing-global-warming%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewhether%20the%20shipping%20industry's%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20efforts%20to%20reduce%20emissions%20were%20having%20the%20counterintuitive%20effect%20of%20worsening%20the%20climate%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20do%20scientists%20know%20what%20the%20climate%20was%20like%20100%2C000%20years%20ago%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESamantha%20Burgess%2C%20Copernicus'%20deputy%20director%2C%20said%20scientists%20at%20the%20organization%20look%20at%20recent%20data%20from%20satellites%3B%20global%20temperature%20records%20dating%20back%20to%201850%3B%20and%20archival%20%26quot%3Bpaleoclimate%20and%20proxy%20data%26quot%3B%20from%20deep-sea%20sediments%2C%20coral%20skeletons%2C%20tree%20rings%2C%20and%20ice%20cores%20around%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20last%20time%20global%20temperatures%20were%20this%20high%20there%20were%20no%20satellites%2C%26quot%3B%20Burgess%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20have%20measured%20the%20concentration%20of%20greenhouse%20gases%20like%20carbon%20dioxide%20and%20methane%20in%20ancient%20ice%20cores%20and%20other%20natural%20sources%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0those%20samples%20create%20a%20record%20of%20what%20the%20atmosphere%20was%20like%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDoes%20this%20mean%20global%20climate%20goals%20are%20unreachable%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENo.%20Countries%20are%20aiming%20to%20limit%20global%20warming%20to%201.5%20degrees%20Celsius%20above%20preindustrial%20levels%2C%20as%20set%20out%20in%20the%202015%20Paris%20Climate%20Agreement.%20While%20the%20average%20temperature%20in%202023%20was%20dangerously%20close%20to%20that%20threshold%2C%20one%20year%20of%20data%20isn't%20enough%20to%20call%20the%20climate%20deal%20a%20failure.%20There%20would%20need%20to%20be%20a%20long-term%20trend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20guidelines%20from%20the%20UN%20Intergovernmental%20Panel%20on%20Climate%20Change%2C%20if%20the%20global%20average%20temperature%20were%20to%20hold%20at%20more%20than%201.5%20degrees%20above%20preindustrial%20levels%20for%20at%20least%20two%20decades%2C%20the%20signatory%20countries%20would%20have%20failed%20to%20uphold%20their%20promise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20likely%20to%20overshoot%201.5%20degrees%2C%26quot%3B%20Burgess%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20basic%20physics%20of%20the%20system%20and%20the%20amount%20of%20warming%20that%20is%20locked%20into%20the%20system.%20However%2C%20the%20reality%20is%20that%20every%20single%20fraction%20of%20a%20degree%20matters.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20some%20researchers%20say%20that%20if%20there%20isn't%20a%20steep%20drop%20in%20emissions%20this%20decade%2C%20that%201.5-degree%20goal%20will%20likely%20be%20a%20lost%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworld-hottest-year-ever-history-climate-crisis-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705008985000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a0057c43bb77284b9c3c2c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworld-hottest-year-ever-history-climate-crisis-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Climate%20scientists%20were%20surprised%20by%20how%20high%20temperatures%20soared%20in%202023.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cboudreau%40insider.com%20(Catherine%20Boudreau)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A538%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworld-hottest-year-ever-history-climate-crisis-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'All%204%20Shankaracharyas%20to%20miss%20Ram%20temple%20event'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705008827000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106740706%2Cimgsize-1213251.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fall-4-shankaracharyas-to-miss-ram-temple-event-two-support-ceremony%2Farticleshow%2F106740703.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TNN%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fall-4-shankaracharyas-to-miss-ram-temple-event-two-support-cere