0engine's%20regular%20liquid%20propellants%2C%20according%20to%20the%20researchers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20essentially%20using%20its%20own%20body%20as%20fuel%2C%20the%20process%20frees%20up%20additional%20space%20on%20the%20rocket%20for%20more%20important%20cargo%2C%20like%20tiny%20nanosatellites%20that%20get%20delivered%20to%20space%2C%20the%20team%20said%20in%20its%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20conventional%20rocket's%20structure%20makes%20up%20between%20five%20and%2012%20percent%20of%20its%20total%20mass.%20Our%20tests%20show%20that%20the%20Ouroborous-3%20can%20burn%20a%20very%20similar%20amount%20of%20its%20own%20structural%20mass%20as%20propellant%2C%26quot%3B%20Patrick%20Harkness%2C%20who%20led%20the%20project%2C%20said%20in%20the%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20could%20make%20at%20least%20some%20of%20that%20mass%20available%20for%20payload%20instead%2C%20it%20would%20be%20a%20compelling%20prospect%20for%20future%20rocket%20designs%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20rocket%20has%20finally%20used%20up%20all%20its%20fuel%2C%20it%20burns%20the%20rest%20of%20itself%20up%20in%20a%20quick%20explosion%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usatoday.com%2Fstory%2Fnews%2Fnation%2F2024%2F01%2F11%2Fuk-glasgow-self-eating-rocket-fuel-video%2F72187085007%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUSA%20Today%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tanks%20of%20traditional%20rockets%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20typically%20become%20space%20debris%20or%20just%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdish-network-fined-first-ever-fcc-enforcement-against-space-junk-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efall%20back%20to%20Earth%3C%2Fa%3E%20once%20they're%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20if%20a%20rocket%20engine%20like%20the%20Ouroborous-3%20can%20be%20used%20regularly%2C%20it%20could%20help%20curb%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftransastra-wins-nasa-